---
const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace(/^\/+|\/+$/g, '') || '';
const citePath = slug ? `/${slug}/` : '/';
---
<footer
  data-pagefind-ignore
  class="mt-16 border-t border-slate-200 bg-white"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-8 text-sm text-slate-600">
    <p>
      Built by <strong>Advocates for School Trust Lands</strong>. Encyclopedia
      content is licensed
      <a
        href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
        rel="license noopener"
        class="text-blue-700 underline hover:text-blue-900"
        >CC&nbsp;BY&nbsp;4.0</a
      >; site code is
      <a
        href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT"
        rel="license noopener"
        class="text-blue-700 underline hover:text-blue-900"
        >MIT</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3">
      Source on
      <a
        href="https://github.com/dave-schooltrustlands/schooltrustlands-encyclopedia"
        rel="noopener"
        class="text-blue-700 underline hover:text-blue-900"
        >GitHub</a
      >. Issues and corrections welcome there.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate-500">
      <span class="font-semibold text-slate-700">Cite as:</span>
      Sullivan and Bird, <em>Schools of the Republic</em> v1.3,
      <span class="break-all">schooltrustlands.net{citePath}</span>, retrieved
      {today}.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">Substrate v1.3.</p>
  </div>
</footer>
